file: crates/ctx-cage/src/runtime.rs
behavior: Resolves the host's Claude Code binary and OAuth subscription credential, and synthesizes a minimal `~/.claude.json` written into the cage rundir so claude auto-detects the bound credential without a login prompt.
edit_notes:
  - Blinding-preserving design: only `.credentials.json` is bound from `~/.claude` (never the whole directory), and the synthesized config carries only `oauthAccount` plus onboarding pre-completion — no host projects/history enter the cage. Any change must preserve this minimality.
  - API traffic depends on `CAGE_BASE_URL` (127.0.0.1:8080) being the in-cage `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL`, routed through a host proxy relay that passes through the `Authorization` header; this file only prepares credentials/config, it does not configure the relay itself.
  - `synth_claude_config` hardcodes onboarding metadata fields (version, timestamps, counts) that mimic a real Claude Code config; if claude's expected config shape changes, these literals need updating.
functions:
  - name: resolve_claude_runtime
    signature: pub fn resolve_claude_runtime(rundir: &Path) -> Result<ClaudeRuntime, CageError>
    purpose: Top-level entry point resolving claude binary, host credentials path, and synthesized config, for a billed cage launch.
  - name: which_claude_realpath
    signature: fn which_claude_realpath() -> Result<PathBuf, CageError>
    purpose: Finds and fully resolves (symlinks) the `claude` binary via `command -v` + `readlink -f`.
  - name: home_credentials_path
    signature: fn home_credentials_path() -> Result<PathBuf, CageError>
    purpose: Locates `$HOME/.claude/.credentials.json`, erroring if the operator hasn't logged in on the host.
  - name: synth_claude_config
    signature: fn synth_claude_config(rundir: &Path) -> Result<PathBuf, CageError>
    purpose: Builds the minimal `~/.claude.json` replacement and writes it to `<rundir>/claude.json`.
invariants:
  - Only the `oauthAccount` field is carried from the host's real `~/.claude.json`; all other host config/project/history data is excluded.
  - Requires `HOME` to be set and `claude` to be on `PATH`; returns `CageError::Protocol` otherwise rather than panicking.
external_deps:
  - serde_json: used both for host config parsing and for hand-building the synthesized config via the `json!` macro.